259
00:22:30.620 --> 00:22:33.790
... and you pay his salary.

260
00:22:34.160 --> 00:22:36.040
And the same employee was murdered
in front of your club.

261
00:22:36.120 --> 00:22:37.750
So yes. legally...

262
00:22:38.870 --> 00:22:42.750
... and unfortunately. it is you
I must ask these questions.

263
00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:46.950
Xanadu is very famous for
its late-night deliveries. right?

264
00:22:48.410 --> 00:22:50.040
What?

265
00:22:50.120 --> 00:22:52.040
Beer. hard liquor. food.

266
00:22:53.370 --> 00:22:54.540
Prostitutes.

267
00:22:54.870 --> 00:22:56.160
Russians and Indians.

268
00:22:57.660 --> 00:22:58.700
And drugs.

269
00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.950
All kinds of drugs. but...
I didn't call you here for that.

270
00:23:06.910 --> 00:23:08.830
I called you here because...

271
00:23:10.700 --> 00:23:13.870
... on nights when your club
is running to peak capacity...

272
00:23:13.950 --> 00:23:15.620
when it's totally full.

273
00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:21.120
you use your emergency
exits as normal entrances.

274
00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:24.040
That means that the
police can never get there...

275
00:23:24.120 --> 00:23:26.450
... and ambulances
can never get there.

276
00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:30.330
Health-safety hazard. hmm?

277
00:23:34.290 --> 00:23:35.580
These are the summons.

278
00:23:36.910 --> 00:23:39.500
You have to pay 1000 rupees fine.
- Okay.

279
00:23:39.580 --> 00:23:41.290
Not here. at the court.

280
00:23:41.410 --> 00:23:45.040
It goes without saying that
you can't leave without telling us.

281
00:23:45.790 --> 00:23:46.910
And why is that?

282
00:23:47.410 --> 00:23:50.870
It's procedure. madam.
One has to adjust.

283
00:23:51.290 --> 00:23:53.660
Like we're making
adjustments for you today.

284
00:24:29.290 --> 00:24:32.000
Sir. sir. sir.

285
00:24:32.040 --> 00:24:33.160
One at a time. please.

286
00:24:33.450 --> 00:24:36.910
Sir. international film festivals and
art exhibitions are happening in Goa.

287
00:24:37.080 --> 00:24:39.700
How can the government encourage
the local artists further?

288
00:24:40.200 --> 00:24:43.660
An encouraging environment
is crucial for an artist.

289
00:24:43.910 --> 00:24:44.580
Correct?

290
00:24:44.660 --> 00:24:46.790
When tourism increases in Goa.
then Goa will prosper.

291
00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:50.000
When Goa prospers. then local artists
will automatically get patronage.

292
00:24:50.040 --> 00:24:51.000
Am I right?

293
00:24:51.040 --> 00:24:54.540
And so. the security
and the system need to be alert.

294
00:24:54.620 --> 00:24:57.750
So sir. as an ex-CM are you dissatisfied
with the current security system?

295
00:24:57.830 --> 00:24:59.330
That's not what I am saying.

296
00:24:59.580 --> 00:25:03.000
I am just saying that every citizen
must understand their responsibility...

297
00:25:03.200 --> 00:25:05.000
... and only then can
we make Goa drug-free.

298
00:25:05.080 --> 00:25:06.750
Otherwise. nothing can happen.

299
00:25:06.830 --> 00:25:08.870
CM Pawaskar cannot do anything alone.

300
00:25:08.950 --> 00:25:10.040
Any CM cannot do anything alone.

301
00:25:10.120 --> 00:25:12.080
They cannot go into
your homes and make a difference.

302
00:25:12.160 --> 00:25:13.250
Right?

303
00:25:13.330 --> 00:25:16.790
Sir. how is the Opposition supporting
the CM's Clean Goa campaign?

304
00:25:16.870 --> 00:25:18.000
Later.

305
00:25:43.700 --> 00:25:45.290
I am ready whenever you are.

306
00:25:45.830 --> 00:25:47.330
So... when do you want to do this?

307
00:25:49.250 --> 00:25:50.870
I need more time.

308
00:25:51.870 --> 00:25:54.000
Whatever you do. do it smartly.

309
00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:56.330
This is not Russia.

310
00:25:57.160 --> 00:25:59.080
This is Goa.

311
00:26:00.450 --> 00:26:02.620
And stop the bloodshed in the streets.

312
00:26:03.540 --> 00:26:06.450
You know very well that
I am not to blame this.

313
00:26:06.540 --> 00:26:10.450
Don't forget that
you don't have much time.

314
00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:18.790
CM Pawaskar.
Does the tone sound familiar?

315
00:26:22.410 --> 00:26:25.000
He is too smart.

316
00:26:27.250 --> 00:26:31.000
He's let ACP Pereira loose

317
00:26:31.080 --> 00:26:33.950
to clean up everything. Full power!

318
00:26:36.040 --> 00:26:38.120
Remember the mid-day meal scheme?

319
00:26:39.580 --> 00:26:46.910
A man who can screw the entire state
assembly over a school's bad food...

320
00:26:48.160 --> 00:26:51.000
... think what he can
do to people like us.

321
00:26:53.160 --> 00:26:55.660
I leave that to your imagination.

322
00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:01.830
Do what you have to quickly.

323
00:27:03.080 --> 00:27:06.080
Even if it means calling someone from
the outside on contract. so be it.

324
00:27:07.120 --> 00:27:09.040
Just clean it all up.

325
00:27:09.700 --> 00:27:14.950
And don't dirty your
F******g hands. for God's sake.

326
00:27:30.250 --> 00:27:34.660
Bhau. we must bring
the situation under control.

327
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:42.000
One has to pour water into
the burrows to bring the rats out.

328
00:27:43.250 --> 00:27:46.290
Otherwise. finding the
box is impossible. Moshe.

329
00:27:46.830 --> 00:27:50.580
We must hire someone
from the outside for this job.

330
00:27:50.950 --> 00:27:53.620
Someone who has no
association with Goa.

331
00:27:54.870 --> 00:27:59.250
The police have their eyes on our men.

332
00:28:01.200 --> 00:28:03.290
It's very tough. Moshe.

333
00:28:04.370 --> 00:28:07.160
By the time an outsider
figures out Goa...

334
00:28:07.250 --> 00:28:09.910
... everyone else pretty
much figures him out.

335
00:28:11.660 --> 00:28:15.080
But I will do something.
- Okay.

336
00:28:22.040 --> 00:28:23.410
Hello?

337
00:28:29.910 --> 00:28:31.330
Where are Ashraf and Imran?

338
00:28:31.410 --> 00:28:32.790
We don't know.

339
00:28:33.330 --> 00:28:34.950
You don't know?
- We don't know.

340
00:28:35.040 --> 00:28:35.950
Then who knows?

341
00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:37.200
We don't know.

342
00:28:38.290 --> 00:28:41.290
Then who knows?
Who knows?

343
00:28:42.330 --> 00:28:44.700
M***********r. do you want me
to shoot you?

344
00:29:17.580 --> 00:29:19.750
Arrest all of them.

345
00:29:57.040 --> 00:29:58.200
Look. man.

346
00:29:59.910 --> 00:30:03.450
We are what boils in our blood.

347
00:30:05.540 --> 00:30:09.040
Our reputation is
what runs in our breath.

348
00:30:10.200 --> 00:30:14.620
And our identity is
what comes from our nature.

349
00:30:17.580 --> 00:30:18.950
Your hands are shaking.

350
00:30:20.410 --> 00:30:23.910
Meaning there's some
vice in your soul.

351
00:30:26.160 --> 00:30:27.830
Forsake this fear.

352
00:30:28.580 --> 00:30:30.950
Forsake this loneliness. Mhatre.

353
00:30:32.250 --> 00:30:35.870
These are qualities
that will send you to hell.

354
00:30:40.790 --> 00:30:44.290
"We must find the path to Paradise."

355
00:30:53.450 --> 00:30:55.750
"And we've found that."

356
00:31:11.790 --> 00:31:14.870
What is this?
Is she preparing for the Olympics?

357
00:31:15.330 --> 00:31:17.250
She's got a great body.

358
00:31:17.540 --> 00:31:19.160
Really tight. eh?

359
00:31:19.250 --> 00:31:21.500
I don't think she needs to diet.

360
00:31:22.040 --> 00:31:24.080
But the boss must
need her for his diet.

361
00:31:24.540 --> 00:31:28.040
For celebration at night
and feast in the morning.

362
00:31:28.790 --> 00:31:32.950
Do you think everything looks
straight for the boss at this age?

363
00:31:33.160 --> 00:31:35.830
These days you get
a gel to straighten your hair...

364
00:31:35.910 --> 00:31:38.830
... and pills for making
everything else hard.

365
00:31:39.870 --> 00:31:41.790
Have you tried?
- No.

366
00:31:42.080 --> 00:31:44.750
These tablets are not
good for the long run.

367
00:31:44.830 --> 00:31:46.790
Porn is the best method.

368
00:31:46.870 --> 00:31:48.370
I don't like watching porn.

369
00:31:49.410 --> 00:31:50.790
It's frustrating.

370
00:31:51.830 --> 00:31:53.540
They keep doing it for over an hour.

371
00:31:54.410 --> 00:31:57.870
And watching their size makes me sad.

372
00:32:00.450 --> 00:32:03.290
Hey... where did she go?

373
00:32:41.410 --> 00:32:43.660
That looks like a very happy drink.

374
00:32:44.450 --> 00:32:45.700
Sorry?

375
00:32:45.790 --> 00:32:47.700
Could you make me one
of those as well?

376
00:32:48.200 --> 00:32:50.330
Don't mind some happy for myself too.

377
00:32:50.700 --> 00:32:52.000
Sure.

378
00:32:52.080 --> 00:32:53.410
I know you.

379
00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:57.200
You're the same girl from yesterday.

380
00:32:57.290 --> 00:32:59.580
You were really checking out Juicy.

381
00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:02.500
Juicy?

382
00:33:02.580 --> 00:33:06.790
You were sitting right outside and
I was with my boyfriend at the beach.

383
00:33:06.870 --> 00:33:09.580
And you girl... you were staring.

384
00:33:10.120 --> 00:33:12.250
That's your boyfriend?

385
00:33:12.950 --> 00:33:14.040
Juicy?

386
00:33:15.660 --> 00:33:17.870
You know that name does suit him.

387
00:33:18.450 --> 00:33:19.540
Sorry.

388
00:33:19.620 --> 00:33:20.660
It's okay.

389
00:33:20.750 --> 00:33:22.120
He is what he is.

390
00:33:22.660 --> 00:33:24.200
You guys look good together.

391
00:33:25.250 --> 00:33:26.830
Yes. we do.

392
00:33:26.910 --> 00:33:30.580
So... does Juicy
have any yummy friends?

393
00:33:34.120 --> 00:33:35.950
Bottoms up. girl!

394
00:33:39.370 --> 00:33:41.200
I am making us another one.

395
00:34:40.040 --> 00:34:44.120
The CM's mission to clean
the drug mafia from Goa...

396
00:34:44.200 --> 00:34:45.870
... is truly commendable.

397
00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:52.000
But will it take more time to fulfill
his promise made during the elections?

398
00:34:55.120 --> 00:34:58.200
I am working as
a f*****g waiter here.

399
00:34:59.330 --> 00:35:02.000
Mom really made a d*******k out
of me by telling me fairy tales.

400
00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:04.580
And even the world
is a bunch of m************s.

401
00:35:06.660 --> 00:35:11.120
You're right. I am in a trap.

402
00:35:11.200 --> 00:35:14.000
Please. don't make me cry.

403
00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:16.200
Smoke this.

404
00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:26.620
I can hear some noises.

405
00:35:28.790 --> 00:35:30.910
Sounds like capsicum.

406
00:35:31.160 --> 00:35:34.830
Bite me. Bite me. Please. Kaanyaa.

407
00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:37.700
F**k that bloody capsicum...

408
00:35:41.700 --> 00:35:43.950
Did Mhatre give you a raise?

409
00:35:49.410 --> 00:35:50.790
Pushkar came over yesterday.

410
00:35:53.250 --> 00:35:55.370
He stripped the entire
staff and trashed everyone.

411
00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:58.080
He trashed you too?

412
00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:01.660
Bloody m***********r.

413
00:36:01.750 --> 00:36:02.950
What was he asking?

414
00:36:06.950 --> 00:36:08.700
Kaanyaa. what was he asking?

415
00:36:10.700 --> 00:36:13.000
The same old - where is Mhatre?
Where is Mhatre?

416
00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:14.830
I am not his wife.

417
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.160
If you must. go and ask at his house.

418
00:36:17.250 --> 00:36:18.950
Why does he trouble us?

419
00:36:20.370 --> 00:36:22.580
Did Mhatre tell you to stay quiet?

420
00:36:23.750 --> 00:36:27.540
What? Is it a big secret?
What happened?

421
00:36:30.580 --> 00:36:31.910
Mhatre is in Sawantwaadi.

422
00:36:32.450 --> 00:36:36.000
Everyone's saying that
there's been a kidnapping.

423
00:36:37.120 --> 00:36:38.750
There's no f*****g kidnapping.

424
00:36:39.540 --> 00:36:41.500
You're spouting nonsense!

425
00:36:42.290 --> 00:36:45.120
Mhatre never saw the kidnapping.
because it never happened.

426
00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:46.790
Stop bullshitting.

427
00:36:46.870 --> 00:36:50.000
Now you're making it all up.

428
00:36:50.500 --> 00:36:55.120
That night. Reddy came over.

429
00:36:55.700 --> 00:36:58.950
And one or two Kashmiris were
already waiting for him.

430
00:37:00.450 --> 00:37:02.250
They were talking about something.

431
00:37:03.120 --> 00:37:06.200
I was watching everything
from a far-off counter.

432
00:37:06.790 --> 00:37:08.450
But I couldn't hear anything.

433
00:37:09.660 --> 00:37:10.450
Roy: Then. did something happen?

434
00:37:10.870 --> 00:37:13.450
What? They were happily chatting.

435
00:37:14.040 --> 00:37:15.000
Roy: And then...

436
00:37:15.080 --> 00:37:17.950
Then they finished
their drinks and left.

437
00:37:19.200 --> 00:37:21.000
Mhatre said he will
give a bonus to everyone.

438
00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:24.500
And that we should lie to everyone.

439
00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:26.080
Roy: He won't give anyone a bonus.

440
00:37:27.040 --> 00:37:29.040
You're my friend.

441
00:37:30.040 --> 00:37:32.250
Don't mention my name anywhere.

442
00:37:33.120 --> 00:37:37.700
Don't worry. brother. Take this.

443
00:37:48.450 --> 00:37:49.620
Will come again.

444
00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:56.750
Boss. Reddy lied.

445
00:37:57.620 --> 00:38:00.500
He was never kidnapped. Yep.

446
00:38:34.290 --> 00:38:37.450
What is it? Huh?

447
00:38:38.290 --> 00:38:39.790
Bloody m***********r

448
00:38:39.870 --> 00:38:41.790
I want Imran and Ashraf.

449
00:38:44.200 --> 00:38:46.750
Check in Aldona.
Check every home.

450
00:38:46.830 --> 00:38:49.950
Every shop.
club. country bar club. on the trees.

451
00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:52.620
under the ground.
but get me Imran anyhow.

452
00:38:53.080 --> 00:38:54.160
Give me a parcel quickly.

453
00:38:56.040 --> 00:38:57.000
Yeah. Bhau?

454
00:38:58.540 --> 00:39:00.580
Mhatre has returned from Sawantwaadi.

455
00:39:02.330 --> 00:39:03.540
Pushya?

456
00:39:03.750 --> 00:39:05.620
Hello?
- Understood. Bhau.

457
00:39:05.700 --> 00:39:09.080
First. talk to him. Shoot later.

458
00:39:09.870 --> 00:39:10.750
Understood?

459
00:39:10.830 --> 00:39:12.250
Understood. Bhau.

460
00:39:23.660 --> 00:39:24.750
Pushkar!

461
00:40:00.330 --> 00:40:01.790
Haven't had a sip of water.

462
00:40:02.660 --> 00:40:04.000
Let me go. Barak.

463
00:40:05.370 --> 00:40:07.200
This is hurting a lot.

464
00:40:11.830 --> 00:40:17.290
You know. it does not
matter whose body it is...

465
00:40:19.290 --> 00:40:21.290
animal or...

466
00:40:24.580 --> 00:40:26.000
human.

467
00:40:28.700 --> 00:40:30.000
The body...

468
00:40:31.660 --> 00:40:34.120
... starts rotting
and then...

469
00:40:36.790 --> 00:40:39.000
... starts emanating a stench.

470
00:40:41.750 --> 00:40:43.330
But when...

471
00:40:45.580 --> 00:40:50.540
... a living human
being starts rotting...

472
00:40:52.830 --> 00:40:57.120
... then even he begins to reek.

473
00:41:04.700 --> 00:41:07.450
I don't know anything.

474
00:41:07.540 --> 00:41:12.200
Then you won't tell me who?

475
00:41:15.870 --> 00:41:17.540
I know...

476
00:41:18.040 --> 00:41:22.700
... when a man's pain
Becomes unbearable...

477
00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:26.160
... he remembers everything.

478
00:41:40.700 --> 00:41:41.870
No.

479
00:42:12.200 --> 00:42:14.370
Now. do you remember?

480
00:42:14.450 --> 00:42:18.290
Will you tell me the entire story now?

481
00:42:19.200 --> 00:42:22.580
Tell me. Tell me.

482
00:42:22.750 --> 00:42:24.000
Tell me!

483
00:42:26.790 --> 00:42:28.000
Reddy.

484
00:42:29.200 --> 00:42:32.620
Reddy looked inside the box.

485
00:42:33.250 --> 00:42:37.290
And he lost his mind.

486
00:42:40.080 --> 00:42:42.830
Hello. Mhatre? Is the bar open?

487
00:42:44.200 --> 00:42:45.450
Keep it open.

488
00:42:59.750 --> 00:43:01.950
The box can be ours.

489
00:43:02.250 --> 00:43:03.870
What do we have to do?

490
00:43:05.040 --> 00:43:08.290
I'll get kidnapped.
the box will get stolen.

491
00:43:09.120 --> 00:43:10.540
We can do it.

492
00:43:11.620 --> 00:43:13.750
But no one will believe
your story. Reddy.

493
00:43:14.250 --> 00:43:16.370
They will if Annappa dies.

494
00:43:19.700 --> 00:43:21.540
Annappa is your right-hand man.

495
00:43:21.700 --> 00:43:24.000
I raised Annappa.

496
00:43:25.160 --> 00:43:28.000
Or else he would've died.

497
00:43:28.700 --> 00:43:33.160
I gave him work when
he was useless.

498
00:43:33.750 --> 00:43:35.330
Now it is time he be useful.

499
00:43:35.660 --> 00:43:39.000
Mhatre. You must disappear.

500
00:43:39.160 --> 00:43:40.660
Everything will settle down later.

501
00:43:40.750 --> 00:43:42.450
Your life will be made!

502
00:43:42.540 --> 00:43:43.700
Okay. Anna.

503
00:43:45.040 --> 00:43:46.290
Keys to the warehouse.

504
00:44:07.660 --> 00:44:09.950
You're still alive.

505
00:44:11.410 --> 00:44:14.540
That means you're going
to have a long life.

506
00:44:14.620 --> 00:44:16.830
A really long life.

507
00:44:20.040 --> 00:44:21.580
Because. after today...

508
00:44:24.580 --> 00:44:28.200
... you will look
after the port business.

509
00:44:28.660 --> 00:44:33.620
Andre. look after him.

510
00:44:34.950 --> 00:44:37.700
Look after him. Andre.

511
00:44:56.000 --> 00:44:57.410
When will he come?

512
00:45:01.410 --> 00:45:02.450
When?

513
00:45:03.450 --> 00:45:05.290
Come. Mhatre sir.

514
00:45:06.830 --> 00:45:08.250
You're looking fresh.

515
00:45:09.000 --> 00:45:11.000
You don't answer calls
on a holiday. do you?

516
00:45:12.450 --> 00:45:15.410
There's network issue
at Sawantvaadi. right?

517
00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:18.120
We must ask the government
to put a new network tower there.

518
00:45:18.200 --> 00:45:20.120
Phone's always unreachable!

519
00:45:20.580 --> 00:45:22.580
Bro. one chilled beer.

520
00:45:23.250 --> 00:45:24.790
Were you drunk?

521
00:45:26.000 --> 00:45:27.080
Where were you?

522
00:45:27.160 --> 00:45:28.790
I was busy working in the fields.

523
00:45:29.250 --> 00:45:30.250
Installing fences.

524
00:45:30.330 --> 00:45:33.700
The wild boars ruined
my crops at night.

525
00:45:33.790 --> 00:45:36.000
